          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇨🇴 Colombia:</strong> The 16th COP to the UN’s Convention on Biological Diversity (COP16) closed <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/environment/20241102-cop16-ends-no-agreement-funding-roadmpa-increase-protect-species" target="_blank">without a funding</a> roadmap after running overtime and losing quorum. Key issues—such as establishing a dedicated biodiversity fund—remain unresolved, mainly due to disagreements between wealthy and developing nations. However, agreements were reached on establishing an Indigenous representation body and sharing benefits from genetic resources. The failure to secure further biodiversity financing follows the urgent findings that over 25% of species are at risk of extinction, pressing concerns as the Kunming-Montreal framework goals loom.</p>
        </mj-text>
